headline: Costco Earnings Reveal 4.5 Million Pies Ahead of Thanksgiving. The Stock Ticks Lower.
summary: While Costco Wholesale posted solid fiscal first-quarter earnings, investors’ reaction was muted, likely a reflection of hopes that the company would post even stronger numbers.  Costco’s earnings per share for the quarter ended Nov. 23 were $4.50.  First-quarter sales—a figure that excludes membership fees—rose 8.2% year over year, the company said.

headline: 3 Large-Cap Stocks That Fall Short
summary: Large-cap stocks have the power to shape entire industries thanks to their size and widespread influence. With such vast footprints, however, finding new areas for growth is much harder than for smaller, more agile players.
